---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How do I hire Alex Maina Mwangi as a developer in Nairobi?',
    answer:
      'You can hire Alex Maina Mwangi directly through the contact form on this site, by email at mainahmwangi12@gmail.com, or via WhatsApp. Alex is a full-stack, frontend, backend, and mobile developer based in Nairobi, Kenya, and is available for both on-site Nairobi projects and remote work worldwide.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What technologies and frameworks does Alex Maina work with?',
    answer:
      'Alex builds production applications with React, Next.js, Vue.js, Node.js, Express, Go, TypeScript, and JavaScript on the web, and Flutter and React Native for mobile. On the backend he works with PostgreSQL, MongoDB, GraphQL, REST APIs, AWS, Docker, and CI/CD pipelines.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can Alex integrate MPESA, Pesapal, or Flutterwave payments?',
    answer:
      'Yes. Alex has shipped multiple Kenyan and pan-African products with MPESA (Daraja), Pesapal, and Flutterwave payment integrations, including STK Push, C2B/B2C flows, and webhook handling for reliable reconciliation.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does Alex Maina build mobile apps for iOS and Android?',
    answer:
      'Yes. Alex develops cross-platform mobile apps for both iOS and Android using Flutter and React Native, delivering native performance from a shared codebase. Shipped apps include Almaza (fintech virtual cards, live on the App Store), TripHoppa, and Jionee Medical.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What kind of projects has Alex Maina worked on?',
    answer:
      'Alex has built luxury travel platforms (Pocket of Paradise), CMA-approved real-estate blockchain tokenization (Yeshara), agentic AI fintech (Mamlaka Hub), peer-to-peer parcel shipping (TripHoppa), mobile diagnostics (Jionee Medical), business directories (Light Growth), and fintech virtual cards (Almaza).',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is Alex Maina available for remote work outside Kenya?',
    answer:
      'Yes. While based in Nairobi, Kenya, Alex works remotely with startups and companies worldwide across compatible time zones, handling end-to-end web and mobile development, API design, and ongoing engineering support.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much experience does Alex Maina have?',
    answer:
      'Alex has 5+ years of professional software engineering experience across startups and SaaS companies, with 10+ products shipped. Teams he has led have achieved a 40% increase in SEO rankings, a 33% improvement in user retention, and a 50% rise in user engagement.',
  },
];

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  '@id': 'https://alexmaina.me/#faq',
  mainEntity: faqs.map((faq) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: faq.question,
    acceptedAnswer: {
      '@type': 'Answer',
      text: faq.answer,
    },
  })),
};
---
<section id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <section class="faq-inner section-inner">
    <h2 id="faq-heading" class="section-heading" data-aos="fade-up">
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h2>
    <div class="faq-list" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item" open={i === 0}>
          <summary class="faq-item__question">
            <span>{faq.question}</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-item__answer">{faq.answer}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
</section>
